node.text:
Happy Halloween! I thought it was perfect to share this recipe and bring you all into the kitchen with me! So easy to make and honestly the best caramel apples I have ever had!😍 
Ingredients: 
5 small apples.
1 cup of maple syrup.
1/3 cup of canned coconut cream 
1 tablespoon of coconut oil 
1 pinch of sea salt. 
Optional Toppings: 
Dark chocolate 
Chopped nuts 
Desiccated coconut 
Peanut butter 

Feliz Halloween! Pensé que era perfecto compartiendo esta receta y te llevará a la cocina conmigo! ¡Es fácil de hacer y honestamente las mejores manzanas de dulces que he tenido! Ingredientes: 5 manzanas pequeñas. 1 taza de jarabe de arce. 1/3 taza de crema de coco enlatada 1 cucharada de aceite de coco 1 con pivote de sal. Topping opcional: chocolate, nueces, mantequilla de maní....

#caramelapples #vegan #plantbased

node.text: 4 months ago we took out our Fijian @namotuisland crew surfing! It was their first time getting out to a real break, let alone on a board. 4 months later and all of them still have the surfing bug and ask me everyday - how are the conditions today and can we go?!! Their faces and joy still fill my heart everyday - another reminder to me that the simple things and sharing the love is what life is all about💛💛💛

node.text:
I came to the Olympics with the dream to win a medal/make Costa Rica proud and to hopefully inspire a little girl to get in the ocean. While I didnt come alway with a medal, I came away with something more. The overwhelming sense of love and honor I have for all the hearts of Costa Rica, all my incredible support crew of family/friends and the magic of sports and the ocean. Shinning a light on the true drive for why I surf and how unity, support, connection is the strongest power of all. ❤️🙏🇨🇷

Vine a los Juegos Olímpicos con el sueño de ganar una medalla y enorgullecer a Costa Rica e inspirar a una niña a meterse en el océano.  No gané una medalla, pero salí con algo más.  El abrumador sentido de amor y honor que tenga para todos los corazones de Costa Rica y mi familia / amigos.  Una motivación de por qué surfeo y cómo la unidad / apoyo es el poder más fuerte de todos.  Gracias por creer en mi.❤️🙏🇨🇷 Un agradecimiento especial por @seanmcgon y @comiteolimpicocr por todo el apoyo y buena energía. #tokyo2020 #olympics #surfing
